-- ── Formbricks ──────────────────────────────────────────────
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Formbricks is an open-source experience management platform for in-product, website, and link surveys, offering self-hosted or EU-hosted cloud deployment as a privacy-first alternative to Qualtrics and Typeform.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium / Open Source$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free (self-hosted or Hobby cloud plan)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2022, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$11-50 employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Kiel, Germany$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$, $q$German$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Formbricks Review 2026: Features, Pricing and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Formbricks review: an open-source survey and experience management platform. See 2026 pricing plans, self-hosting options, features, and alternatives.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Formbricks is an open-source experience management platform built around in-product surveys, website surveys, and link-based surveys, positioned explicitly as a privacy-first, self-hostable alternative to enterprise experience-management incumbents like Qualtrics and to consumer-friendly hosted survey tools like Typeform and SurveyMonkey. The product's origin traces back to an earlier project called snoopForms, which the founding team rebranded and relaunched as Formbricks, broadening its scope from a narrower form tool into a fuller survey and experience-management platform with targeting, segmentation, and in-app feedback capabilities. Formbricks was founded in 2022 in Kiel, Germany, by Johannes Dancker, who serves as CEO, and Matti Nannt, who serves as co-founder and CTO, and the company has continued to operate out of Germany with a strong open-source, developer-first identity that has helped it build a community around its GitHub repository alongside its commercial cloud offering. The company's earliest institutional backing came from a pre-seed round led by OSS Capital, a venture fund that specializes specifically in open-source software companies, which is a meaningful signal about Formbricks' strategic identity: rather than treating open source as a marketing tactic layered on top of an otherwise closed product, Formbricks has built its core application under the AGPLv3 open-source license, meaning the fully functional core, covering link surveys, website surveys, and in-app surveys, can be used for free for both personal and commercial use, self-hosted on a company's own infrastructure via Docker. This licensing and deployment model directly addresses a persistent pain point for privacy-conscious and compliance-sensitive teams, particularly in Europe, who are often reluctant to send customer feedback and product usage data to third-party, US-hosted survey platforms subject to different data protection regimes. For teams that prefer a managed option without operating their own infrastructure, Formbricks also offers a hosted cloud version, run out of Frankfurt, Germany, that is GDPR-compliant and EU-hosted by design, an explicit alternative to survey platforms that host data primarily in the United States. Formbricks' feature set spans the core survey-building capabilities expected of any modern experience-management tool, including a broad library of question types, conditional logic and branching, hidden fields for passing contextual data into a survey, support for partial response capture, recall of previously collected information within a survey flow, multimedia backgrounds, and file upload questions, alongside single-use links for controlled distribution. Beyond core survey building, the platform supports respondent identification and contact and segment management, letting product and growth teams target specific in-app surveys to particular user segments based on behavioral or account attributes rather than showing the same survey to every user, a capability that is central to in-product research and feedback-collection use cases like NPS surveys, feature-adoption research, or churn-risk interviews triggered by specific in-app behavior. The platform also offers native iOS and Android SDKs for triggering and displaying surveys inside mobile apps, a full REST API for programmatic survey management, custom webhooks for pushing response data into other systems, and AI-assisted translation for running the same survey across multiple languages without manually managing every translated variant. On the pricing side, Formbricks follows a freemium model with meaningful free-tier capability rather than a token trial. The Hobby plan is free and includes one workspace and up to 250 survey responses per month, along with the same underlying feature set as the paid plans for core survey types. The Pro plan, marketed as the platform's most popular tier, costs $74 per month and includes three workspaces, 2,000 monthly responses, unlimited team seats, the ability to remove Formbricks branding from surveys, respondent identification, contact and segment management, all available integrations, email follow-ups, custom webhooks, the iOS and Android SDKs, and AI-powered translation. The top Scale plan costs $325 per month and includes five workspaces, 5,000 monthly responses, team and access-role management, quota management for controlling how many responses a given segment can contribute, feedback unification across multiple sources, AI-based topic and subtopic labeling of open-text responses, custom dashboards and charts, two-factor authentication, and spam protection via reCAPTCHA. Formbricks offers annual billing with a two-month-free discount across paid plans, and a 14-day free trial of Pro-tier features is available with no credit card required. Reported revenue figures place Formbricks at roughly $550,000 in annual recurring revenue with a valuation of approximately $3 million as of the most recently disclosed figures, positioning it as a still-early-stage but revenue-generating open-source SaaS company rather than a pre-revenue project. Formbricks' target audience spans two overlapping groups: product and growth teams at software companies who want in-product survey and feedback tooling comparable to what Qualtrics or Typeform offer but without vendor lock-in or per-response pricing that scales unpredictably, and privacy- or compliance-driven organizations, particularly in Europe, that need a GDPR-native or fully self-hosted survey solution for regulatory or data-sovereignty reasons. Competitively, Formbricks sits between fully open-source, developer-oriented form tools with narrower feature sets and heavyweight enterprise experience-management suites like Qualtrics, aiming to offer enterprise-grade capability, segmentation, quota management, AI-assisted analysis, at a fraction of the cost and with the option of full self-hosted data control that neither Typeform nor Qualtrics can match.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'c6b896e4-5bf3-4a3c-9f83-469792152818';

